attributes.Long form description: The student starts the Marius assembling by placing the legs one on top of the other in a crossed way, then he joins the legs by screwing with a wrench the hex nut to the bolt located in the center, then the student has to assemble the legs to the seat and for this accidentally confuses the order of assembly so the instructor asks to change the order by first placing the legs on the seat, once the student corrects the order, he is able to systematically screw the four corresponding screws to the legs of the seat, screws that are extracted from the bag he has at the side, once finished, finally the student turn the chair over to tighten the hex nut a little more.

attributes.Transcription: Hello, In front of you, you will see the parts needed to assemble the Marius IKEA stool.
The task for you will be to please build this stool.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student should place both feet vertically on the table.

attributes.Transcription: Please place both feet vertically on the table.
Please also take the nut, metal nut from the parts bag.

attributes.Conversation Purpose: instructor-start-conversation_adjusting to capture better quality video

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student should make sure to not over tighten the nut.

attributes.Transcription: Please make sure to not over tighten the nut.

attributes.Conversation Purpose: instructor-start-conversation_adjusting to capture better quality video
attributes.Transcription: Additionally please make sure to keep both of your hands take along view.

attributes.Action sentence: The student assembles the legs on the seat.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student begins in the wrong order to attach the seat to the leg.

attributes.Transcription: Please place the baseboard on the table.
Place the feet on top of it.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student inserts the screw on the leg without first putting the saddle washer on.

attributes.Transcription: Before screwing in the screws, please place a plastic washer underneath the screw.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student accidentally slipped the washer

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student inserts incorrectly the screw into the saddle washer.

attributes.Transcription: Please flip the screw and the washer.

attributes.Action sentence: The student tightens the middle hex nut on the bolt.

attributes.Transcription: Lastly, please tighten the central screw.
Thank you very much,That concludes everything for this task.
You may now go ahead and press the stop button.
